H0.text: Named from the Gaelic for elbow, what is the name of the Irish bagpipes played by squeezing air with the arm. Caoimhin

H1.text: Named from the Gaelic for elbow, what is the name of the Irish bagpipes played by squeezing air with the arm. Feadóg

H2.text: Named from the Gaelic for elbow, what is the name of the Irish bagpipes played by squeezing air with the arm. Píob

H3.text: Named from the Gaelic for elbow, what is the name of the Irish bagpipes played by squeezing air with the arm. Uilleann

A4.text: Uilleann is a genitive form of the Irish word for 'elbow', uillinn.

A5.text: The Irish term for uilleann pipes is píb uilleann (alt. píob uilleann), which means 'pipes(s) of the elbow(s)’
